RetryDeliveryResponse.description:
Response for POST /v1/webhooks/{id}/deliveries/{delivery_id}/retry (202 Accepted).

The original event_id is preserved so downstream consumers can detect the retry;
a fresh delivery_id is assigned for the new attempt.

put.description:
write or overwrite a KV entry.

Body: {"value": <any>, "type": "json"|"text"|"blob", "ttl_at"?: <iso8601>}

Returns {key, value_type, size}. 413 on oversize. 403 without kv:write scope.

post.description:
acknowledge delivered items.

Body: {"ids": [.item IDs.]}
Returns {acked: N}.

enqueue URLs.

Body: {"urls": [.], "dedup"?: true}

Returns {added: N}. 429 when queue cap exceeded.
